snippet.textDisplay:
Bernie's proposals aren't just the most ethical policies they also make the most financial sense. For all those people screaming "SOCIALISM!!!", I would like to know whether you favor getting rid of Medicare for people 65+ or Medicaid for the indigent, or public K-12, fire department, military, police department, postal service, etc. These are all programs that are no more socialist than Medicare for All or College For All. It's the same rationale: There are certain things that are of such great potential benefit to our society and which make sense to fund through taxation because it's much cheaper and we all reap the benefits - directly or indirectly. About the specific policies:


1. We already have Medicare for 65+. He wants to expand that to cover all of us. Having a single insurer negotiating with drug companies, hospitals, labs, and device companies would bring our health care costs down to where every other OECD countries' are. I'm an M.D. and I see so many patients who delayed care due to lack of insurance, high copays, or deductibles. These patients end up in much worse shape or dead. Their care also costs much more when these ailments are treated more acutely rather than early. All healthcare economics research bears this out.
2. We already have public K-12 but the share of jobs in the job market that can sustain a person wanting to own a home and support a family are increasingly requiring higher education. All the while, college debt is crushing the segment of our population that should be the most economically active. This debt bubble is set to explode soon. Free 2-4 year college and student debt cancellation would be a massive boost to the economy and huge relief to the demographic that has the weight of this countries future on it's shoulders. It's also not nearly as expensive as people think. Total outstanding student debt is $1.5 trillion. Total spent on wars in the Middle East since 2001 is $5.9-6.4 trillion and counting!
3. Green New Deal. You either believe the climate scientists or you think it's a big conspiracy to get those sweet sweet research grants (ignoring the fact that a great deal of climate skeptics are bankrolled by fossil fuel companies (look up ExxonMobil and ALEC funding of skeptics) If you believe the experts, you know we have very little time to turn things around and avoid catastrophe. Crop failure, heat waves, unpredictable weather patterns, mass migration and the xenophobic conflicts/wars that will emerge from that. Only the Green New Deal is substantive enough to address this existential crisis. If you believe the expert and you have kids or grandkids or just care about the future of organized human life on Earth, then you should be behind the Green New Deal. Anything else is just nihilistic or naive.
